<br>
What are the procedures for certifying a record catch from a Catch and Release Area?<br>
<br>
If trophy trout do in fact hang out in Trophy Trout Areas, what happens if you managed to catch a 26&quot; Brook Trout that would obviously be a new Arkansas state record?  Would a picture and measurement be enough?  I understand that normally a representative of the AF&amp;GC is required to be present at a weighing.  Should there be (or is there) another category for C&amp;R records?<br>
<br>
I think it is important for the Trophy Trout Areas to be found to actually produce trophy trout, I mean, that needs to be made known. <br>
<br>
Enquiring minds want to know...<br>
<br>
Holland <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=howardsmith@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Howard Smith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#000000>(9/8/03 6:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Seems that I heard of some special way for C&amp;R areas, but I just can't remember any details. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=holland@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Holland</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#000000>(9/8/03 6:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Howard that is exactly where I'm coming from.  I know I've heard something about this, but darned if I can remember the details. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drifter@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Drifter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#000000>(9/9/03 6:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Talked to an ex-commissioner and the trout biologist last night and they both said there is now no way to certify a record catch in the C&amp;R area. If you went by Arkansas' present format, even if you brought the scale to the river, you would be violating the regs. In C&amp;R you must release the fish immediately, or soon after, ie; pictures. Waiting for a AGFC member or scale or both would have you holding the fish too long. They both want to see a way to certify C&amp;R records. Helps prove they are working. Maybe photos, witnesses and measurements. They both said a weight classification probably wouldn't work. A length plus girth class would be best. Maybe an IGFA system with line weights included but that may be too complicated. Keep asking and push for a system and from what I heard it could be a reality. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flyfishar>FlyFishAR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 526<br> <font color=#000000>(9/9/03 6:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.flyfishingarkansas.com/Photo%20Gallery/tn_j.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> The regulations state that &quot;All fish caught in the C&amp;R areas must be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>immediately</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> released&quot;. I called the enforcement office and asked them what the term &quot;immediate&quot; meant. They said &quot;What do you think it means? It means immediate&quot;. I know that most of the biologists would like to see a new world record caught on any of the rivers. I wouldn't suggest that anyone break the law,......... but I just wonder what would happen.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chofujohn@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>chofujohn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#000000>(9/10/03 1:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> world record...</span><hr size=1> Hi John,<br>
<br>
I appreciate your stating you'd not encourage anyone breaking the law, BUT...  Would it be breaking the law to leave the fish in the water hooked and then hop in your boat and very gently and slowly move downstream where you land the fish out of the CR area?  He isn't caught until he's landed, I'll assume.  I know it's far fetched and probably not consistent with the laws of the land, at least not technically, but the question was on the table.  lol  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
<br>
John Dent <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maddog48>maddog48</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#000000>(9/10/03 2:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Proposal</span><hr size=1> John, what would be the chance of some sort of proposal going to the G&amp;FC to make an amendment on the release? If the fishery biologists are wanting a record that badly, something has to be changed...which shouldn't be that hard for a comittee to figure out. See you in a few weeks.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mike <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maddog48>maddog48</A> at: 9/10/03 5:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flyfishar>FlyFishAR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br>  Posts: 529<br> <font color=#000000>(9/10/03 8:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.flyfishingarkansas.com/Photo%20Gallery/tn_j.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Proposal</span><hr size=1> The biologists I have talked with are proposing something like a release technique that would deal with fish over 30 inches that would allow for measurement, pictures, and release. I have some equipment that &quot;might&quot; be allowed under the current enforcement acts. I have yet to have the &quot;opportunity&quot; to test the system though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I would encourage all of you to suggest a system to our current comission. I think it would be good for Arkansas, good for the fishery, and ultimately good for all of us to have &quot;another&quot; world record from Arkansas.<br>
<br>
John <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=159.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showNextMessage?topicID=159.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=159.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/addReply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.emailToFriend?topicID=159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.threadControl?topicID=159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=159.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub98.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cells